The paper discusses planning for multiagent systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of partial-order planning and the modification of the STRIPS action representation language suggest that the paper may also be relevant to planning (cs.PL) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the focus on cooperative multiagent systems suggests that the paper may be relevant to the subfield of multiagent systems (cs.MA). Finally, the use of algorithms and the development of a planner suggest that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG).
